Title: A Global Analog of Cheshire Charge

Authors: Patrick McGraw

Comments: 24 pages (figures 1-4 included as uu-encoded tar files), CALT-68-1865

corrected; some typos and sign mismatches are removed.)Journal-ref: Phys.Rev. D50 (1994) 952-961

It is shown that a model with a spontaneously broken global symmetry cansupport defects analogous to Alice strings, and a process analogous to Cheshirecharge exchange can take place. A possible realization in superfluid He-3 ispointed out.